canonical:
  title: 西樓觀雪
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 怒嶺嵬岑繞郭來橫空萬疊玉成堆水仙向曉遊何處江上銀屛邐迤開
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 西樓觀雪
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 怒嶺嵬岑繞郭來。橫空萬疊玉成堆。水仙向曉遊何處。江上銀屛邐迤開。
korean:
  title: 서루 관설
  author: 김극기
  language: kor
  text: |-
    높은 뫼 성낸 마루 성곽을 에워 싸니
    반공에 비낀 만첩 백옥더미 이뤘구나
    수선은 새벽에 어디에 노는고
    강 위에 은 병풍이 구불구불 펼쳤구나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_020_0720&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Watching Snow from the Western Tower
  author: Kim Geuk-gi
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Fierce peaks and jagged crags circle the walls,
    Across the vast sky, ten thousand layers pile like white jade.
    Where do the water sprites wander at dawn?
    Silver screens unfold in rippling waves upon the river.
  footnotes:
    - Water sprites (수선) may refer to celestial beings or immortals, here suggesting the magical quality of the snowy landscape at daybreak.
    - The 'silver screens' (은 병풍) is a poetic image for the snow-covered riverbank reflecting light like polished metal.
